.TH "bcm2835_spi_prepare_sg" 9 "bcm2835_spi_prepare_sg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bcm2835_spi_prepare_sg \- prepare and submit DMA descriptor for sglist
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bcm2835_spi_prepare_sg
.BI "(struct spi_controller *ctlr "  ","
.BI "struct spi_device *spi "  ","
.BI "struct spi_transfer *tfr "  ","
.BI "struct bcm2835_spi *bs "  ","
.BI "bool is_tx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctlr" 12
SPI master controller
.IP "spi" 12
SPI slave
.IP "tfr" 12
SPI transfer
.IP "bs" 12
BCM2835 SPI controller
.IP "is_tx" 12
whether to submit DMA descriptor for TX or RX sglist
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Prepare and submit a DMA descriptor for the TX or RX sglist of \fItfr\fP.
Return 0 on success or a negative error number.
